### Login
# Authenticates a user and returns a short-lived access token (15 min).
# Also sets an HttpOnly refresh token cookie (7 days) for silent re-auth.
# Public endpoint — no Authorization header required.
# Use the returned token as JWT_TOKEN in your env for authenticated requests.
POST {{BASE_URL}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "admin@example.com",
  "password": "change-me-on-first-login"
}

###

### Create User
# Creates a new user and returns a signup link containing a short-lived JWT.
# The signup link should be sent to the new user so they can set their password.
# Requires a valid Bearer JWT (auth token) in Authorization header.
POST {{BASE_URL}}/api/auth/create-user
Authorization: Bearer {{JWT_TOKEN}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "newuser@example.com",
  "name": "New User"
}

###

### Set Password
# Sets the new user's password using the signup token from the signup link.
# Returns a short-lived access token and sets a refresh token cookie.
# Requires the signup token (from the signup link) in Authorization header.
POST {{BASE_URL}}/api/auth/set-password
Authorization: Bearer {{SIGNUP_TOKEN}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "password": "mysecurepassword",
  "confirmPassword": "mysecurepassword"
}

###

### Change Password
# Changes the current user's password. Requires the correct current password.
# Returns a fresh access token and rotates the refresh token cookie.
# Requires a valid Bearer auth token in Authorization header.
POST {{BASE_URL}}/api/auth/change-password
Authorization: Bearer {{JWT_TOKEN}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "currentPassword": "mysecurepassword",
  "newPassword": "mynewsecurepassword",
  "confirmPassword": "mynewsecurepassword"
}

###

### Refresh
# Exchanges the HttpOnly refresh token cookie for a new short-lived access token.
# The refresh token is rotated — a new cookie is set on each successful call.
# No Authorization header needed — the browser sends the cookie automatically.
POST {{BASE_URL}}/api/auth/refresh

###

### Logout
# Revokes the current refresh token and clears the cookie.
# Call this when the user explicitly logs out.
POST {{BASE_URL}}/api/auth/logout

